Topics covered in the practical course:
I Absorption spectra and determination of extinction coefficient. Determination of analyte concentration by spectrophotometry and titration.
II. Photometric methods for protein concentration determination.
III. The acid-base properties of amino acids. Buffer solutions. Protein solubility.
IV. Purification of α-amylase with gel filtration chromatography. Assay of enzymatic activity and substrate specificy of enzymes.
V. The effect of pH, temperature and enzyme concentration on invertase reaction. The effect of inhibition on kinetic parameters.
VI. Substrate specificy of alcohol dehydrogenase. Kinetic parameters on different substrates.
VII. Protein purification with ion exchange chromatography and analysis with SDS polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of basic methods used in biochemistry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected: - to be able to use basic labware used in biochemical experiments. - to be familiar with basic methods in biochemistry. - to be able to interpret the results of the experiment and to compose a report.
